The following components are taken from the OpenWRT project, who
actually did all the work of making our target hardware
supported.  Those guys are AWESOME.

diag:

Provides the "diag" kernel module, which provides a GPIO driver.
Among other things, this turns on the hard disk and LEDs when
installed in the kernel on a WL-700gE.  Taken from broadcom-diag
in SVN revision ????.

trx:

The "trx" image construction program, taken from OpenWRT's
firmware-utils package as of SVN revision 7491.

lzma-loader:

The "lzma-loader" program, used to load and decompress an
LZMA-compressed kernel image.  Taken from OpenWRT as of SVN
revision 11340.
